In this letter, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. informs the Speaker of the House (or Madam President) about recent military action. The President states that the action was taken to protect US citizens and advance national security and foreign policy interests. The military action was authorized under the War Powers Resolution, the 2001 Authorization for Use of Military Force, and the Authorization for Use of Military Force Against Iraq. The President asserts that the action was necessary, proportionate, and in accordance with international law and the United States' right of self-defense. The President also expresses readiness to take further action if needed and thanks Congress for their support.